New Ubuntu 16.04 setup guideline

## Update the system

* sudo apt-get update
* sudo apt-get -y upgrade

## Install RVM and Ruby(both RMI and JRuby) 

* gpg --keyserver hkp://keys.gnupg.net --recv-keys 409B6B1796C275462A1703113804BB82D39DC0E3
* curl -sSL https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable
* source ~/.rvm/scripts/rvm
* close terminal and reopen
* In edit/profile preference, check Run command as a login shell
* cd ~ && sudo nano .gemrc
* Inside .gemrc insert gem: --no-rdoc --no-ri
* Save and exit. 
* rvm install 2.3.3
* rvm use 2.3.3@global --default
* gem install bundler
* gem install passenger
* rvm install jruby-9.1.5.0
* rvm use jruby-9.1.5.0@global
* gem install bundler
* gem install torquebox-server

## Install Node, React and Angular 2

* curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_6.x | sudo -E bash - (Install node v6 for angular 2 to work)
* sudo apt-get install -y nodejs  
* sudo npm install -g @angular/cli
* sudo npm install -g create-react-app

## Install and configure Git 

* sudo apt-get install git
* git config --global color.ui true
* git config --global user.name "zabir88"
* git config --global user.email "zabir8809@gmail.com"
* cd ~ && mkdir .ssh (if no .ssh directory exists)
* ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "zabir8809@gmail.com"
* cat id_rsa.pub and paste it to github account

## Install Sublime text editor

* sudo add-apt-repository ppa:webupd8team/sublime-text-3
* sudo apt-get update
* sudo apt-get install sublime-text-installer
* Install package manger
* Install the following packages: File Icon, Agila Theme, All AutoComplete, Babel, Emmet, HTML2Haml, Sass, SideBarEnhancements, TypeScript, 

## Install PGAdmin3 from software center

## Install PostgreSQL

* sudo apt-get update
* sudo apt-get install -y postgresql postgresql-contrib libpq-dev  
* sudo -u postgres createuser -s zabir (name the user same as machine user)
* sudo -u postgres psql
* \password zabir (to set password for the user created)

## Install Unity Tweak Tool, Chrome, Contacts, Calendar, Stacer

## Sync online account(google) with ubuntu
 
## cd ~ && mkdir .themes (unzip custom themes in this folder to get access from Unity Tweak Tool)

## Add Files, Mozilla, Chrome, Sublime, Geddit, Calendar, Contacts, Calculator, PgAdmin3, Software Center to Dock.


